list.abstract: Minute（英[ˈmɪnɪt , maɪˈnjuːt]，美[ˈmɪnɪt , maɪˈnjuːt]），英语单词，作名词用，为分；会议记录；议事录。作形容词用，为微小的；异常小的；极小的。作动词用，为将（会议事项）记入议事录；记录；以备忘录方式告知。短语搭配有just a minute（稍等片刻；且慢）。例句为“They'll be all right in a minute.（他们马上就好）”。 Minute名词类近义词有cent、moments、note等，形容词类近义词有tiny、strict、micro等。
Minute是一个英文单词，通常作名词，意思是“分钟，片刻”，也可做及物动词，形容词，意思分别是“纪录”，”精细的“。

yingyinNormal.en: Just listen for a minute.
yingyinNormal.zh: 听一分钟。

yingyinNormal.en: One minute I'm here with you, and the next...
yingyinNormal.zh: 上一分钟我还和你在一起，而下一分钟...

yingyinNormal.en: Hi. I'm gonna need a minute.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你好。给我一分钟。

yingyinNormal.en: Now is exactly 1 minute till tea time.
yingyinNormal.zh: 现在距离下午茶时间，正好还有整整一分钟。
yingyinNormal.videoNameZh: 《爱丽丝梦游仙境2：镜中奇遇记》

yingyinNormal.en: You wouldn't last a minute on the Serengeti.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你要是在塞伦盖蒂连一分钟都撑不到。

yingyinNormal.en: Tetrodotoxin B. Slows the pulse to one beat a minute.
yingyinNormal.zh: 河豚毒素B，能把脉搏降到一分钟一跳。

yingyinNormal.en: What's taking you boys so long? In a minute. In a minute? What's gonna happen in a minute?
yingyinNormal.zh: 你们怎么那么久？再一分钟就好。“一分钟”？一分钟内会发生什么事？

yingyinNormal.en: That wasn't a minute.
yingyinNormal.zh: 还没到一分钟呢。
yingyinNormal.videoNameZh: 《爱丽丝梦游仙境2：镜中奇遇记》

yingyinNormal.en: When you're in somewhere like the Amazon, one minute it could be boiling hot and then the next minute it would be, you know, torrential rain.
yingyinNormal.zh: 当身处亚马逊这样的地方时，前一分钟可能会酷热难耐，后一分钟可能就会有瓢泼大雨。
yingyinNormal.videoNameZh: 《大卫·贝克汉姆：探索未知之境》

yingyinNormal.en: Just give us a minute. Oh, take all the time you need.
yingyinNormal.zh: 就给我们一分钟。你们慢慢谈。

yingyinNormal.en: So, your question. What is it? You have exactly one minute.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你，你的问题是什么？你的时间只有一分钟。
yingyinNormal.videoNameZh: 《爱丽丝梦游仙境2：镜中奇遇记》

yingyinNormal.en: Okay. I'll give you one chance to change my mind. You got one minute.
yingyinNormal.zh: 好，我给你机会改变我的看法，计时1分钟。

yingyinNormal.en: Mom, it's all I've ever wanted since I heard about it a minute ago.
yingyinNormal.zh: 妈妈，这是我一分钟前听到后唯一想要的东西。

yingyinNormal.en: Ticket？Are we gonna make up the ten minute？We gonna try, Sir.
yingyinNormal.zh: 您的票。晚点的十分钟能追回来吧。先生，我们尽量。

yingyinNormal.en: I am only one man. Okay Ross, time is up. No, just give me another minute.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我只有一个人，好了，时间到。再给我一分钟。

yingyinNormal.en: Hey. Here's the sewing kit you asked for. Ooh! A minute, 19. Quick.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这是你要的针线包。只花了1分钟19秒。速度惊人。

yingyinNormal.en: It's a music playing device. Okay. We'll get to that in a minute.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这是一个音乐播放设备。好了，一分钟后我们会看到它。

yingyinNormal.en: Although it did get exciting for a minute when Amy inhaled a wool ball.
yingyinNormal.zh: 虽然艾米误吸进一个羊毛球时我稍微开心了一分钟。

yingyinNormal.en: What about installing the security profile? Well. That's gonna be like a minute tops.
yingyinNormal.zh: 替换安全资料的时间呢？这个用最多一分钟。

yingyinNormal.en: They're fond of arrows dipped in a neurotoxin that'll stop your heart in one minute.
yingyinNormal.zh: 他们箭上的毒能麻痹神经，一分钟内就能要你的命。

examination_example.sentence: To accurately tell whether someone is sociable, studies show, we need at least a <highlight>minute</highlight>, preferably five.

word_usage.usage:
in a minute表示“马上，立刻”，其中的不定冠词不能改成定冠词。
示例：他马上就来帮忙。
误 He will come to give me his hand in the minute.
正 He will come to give me his hand in a minute.

英语中习惯把表示时间、金钱、距离等的短语看作是一个整体，故谓语动词须用单数。
示例：完成这项练习，5分钟时间并不算长。
误 Five minutes are not a long time to complete this exercise.
正 Five minutes is not a long time to complete this exercise.

较 minute 所表示的时间短, 指一刹那或一段很短时间。有时也含持续的意味。

示例：他马上就来帮忙。
误 He will come to give me his hand in the minute.
正 He will come to give me his hand in a minute.

英语中习惯把表示时间、金钱、距离等的短语看作是一个整体，故谓语动词须用单数。
示例：完成这项练习，5分钟时间并不算长。
误 Five minutes are not a long time to complete this exercise.
正 Five minutes is not a long time to complete this exercise.
